                <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-6">
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 italic">In the power adapter industry, safety isn't just a feature —it's a legal shield for your brand. With GaN chargers pushing higher wattages in smaller shells, understanding thermal and electrical safety has never been more critical.</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">Between 2025 and 2026, the US Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) recalled over <strong>447,000 chargers</strong> linked to fire and burn hazards —involving <strong>112 incidents</strong> and <strong>1 fatality</strong>. In a separate incident, HTRC and Haisito battery chargers were recalled after <strong>33 reported fires and explosions</strong> affecting 4,800 units, causing 3 injuries and $224,000 in property damage. Approximately 40% of first-time certification submissions fail at least one critical safety test. Understanding charger safety standards is not optional —it is a market access requirement.</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">WOWOHCOOL breaks down the essential certifications for global markets. For a step-by-step walkthrough of US and EU certification requirements, see our <a href="/blog/certifications-us-eu-guide" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">US & EU charger certification guide</a>.</p>
