<!-- Section 4: Protection Mechanisms -->
<section id="protection-mechanisms" class="mb-16">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">4. Critical Protection Mechanisms</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Inside every quality charger, multiple protection layers work redundantly —if one fails, another takes over. Each layer addresses a specific failure mode identified through decades of industry data.</p>

<div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
<table class="w-full text-sm border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
<thead class="bg-brandBlue text-white">
<tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-black uppercase">Protection</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-black uppercase">What It Does</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-black uppercase">Why It Matters</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody class="bg-white">
<tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-4 font-bold text-brandBlue">OVP</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Prevents device burnout during voltage spikes</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Eliminates liability claims</td></tr>
<tr class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50"><td class="p-4 font-bold text-brandBlue">SCP</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Instant shutdown for damaged cables or ports</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Required for Amazon acceptance</td></tr>
<tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-4 font-bold text-brandBlue">OTP</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Thermal throttling before overheating</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Essential for GaN chargers</td></tr>
<tr class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50"><td class="p-4 font-bold text-brandBlue">FOD</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Detects metal near wireless charging coils</td><td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Wireless charger safety</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
